name: Vegan Agave Cornbread Muffins
author: smiithh
summary: This vegan cornbread is made with whole-wheat flour and sweetened with agave syrup. It got votes as being better than traditional cornbread muffins by my anti-vegan roommates! They can also be made macrobiotic if you substitute the agave with maple syrup.
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C)
Combine the cornmeal, flour, baking soda, and salt in a large bowl; stir in the applesauce, soy milk, and agave nectar
Slowly add the oil while stirring
Pour the mixture into the muffin pan
Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick or small knife inserted in the crown of a muffin comes out clean, 15 to 20 minutes
